{
  "stem": "7455.2",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So when they hoped that the Germans will occupy Poland, if they collaborate with the Germans, when the Germans come to Poland, in reciprocation, they'll give them that part, though they had underground activities and [? dreamed ?].",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We did not know-- we did not realize that calling that puppy Hitler agitated our Ukrainians.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That was a blunder.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Even though we changed the name on our own, that we loved our puppy, it was too late.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They couldn't help saying, why wouldn't Abraham or Moses not be more appropriate?",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We w-- we knew that, God forbid, if the German would come, they would point at us out.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "At one time, we went visiting our relatives.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And upon our return, we opened the gate, and at the foot of the steps laid our dog, outstretched, dead, poisoned.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The children, we were hysterical-- crying, frightened.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But more frightened were my parents.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "That was symbolic.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "That dog had to die, even though they heard we called him Rex, because that was an insult to their fuhrer, to Hitler.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And we had a foreboding of danger.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But time elapsed, and we had the Russians.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "The Russians came, which I'm sure the Ukrainians anticipated the Germans to march in.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And now the Russ-- the Germans are about to enter.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "We are being-- we are in church, in a Ukrainian church, not feeling so comfortable, but they let us be there.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And it was more insulting that our dog would crawl away and crawl near the statues, which is improper.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "We laid there on blankets at the church, and bombs were falling.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And the church is high, so the impact is stronger.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And glass is falling down, and we are huddling.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
